headline: Abercrombie earnings, ADP data, Trump address: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime's Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton review the top market coverage and economic data that Wall Street will be paying attention to tomorrow, Wednesday, March 5. Retailers Abercrombie & Fitch (ANF) and Foot Locker (FL) are expected to post their latest earnings results Wednesday morning, with corporate earnings also expected out from companies like Campbell’s (CPB), Marvell Technology (MRVL), and Zscaler (ZS) throughout the day. Ahead of the February jobs report this Friday, ADP will be releasing the latest private sector employment data. Mortgage applications data are also due out tomorrow. Lastly, President Trump will address a joint session of Congress Tuesday night. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: California BanCorp And 2 More High Growth Companies Insiders Favor
summary: As the U.S. stock market grapples with the impact of newly imposed tariffs and economic uncertainty, investors are closely watching sectors that might offer resilience amid volatility. In such an environment, companies with strong insider ownership can be appealing, as they often signal confidence from those most familiar with the business's prospects and operations.
